  "prompt": "What will be one word for \"make an example of\" idiom?",
  "response": "A suitable single word that conveys the essence of the idiom \"make an example of\" is **\"exemplify.\"**\n\n**Exemplify** means to illustrate or clarify by giving an example, and it can capture the idea of using someone or something as a representative instance to demonstrate a point or establish a precedent. \n\n**Example in a sentence:**\n- The manager decided to **exemplify** the consequences of tardiness by addressing the issue with the consistently late employee during the team meeting.\n\nWhile \"exemplify\" primarily focuses on illustrating or demonstrating, it aligns closely with the intent behind \"make an example of,\" especially in contexts where the goal is to set a precedent or serve as a warning to others.",
